- **Documentation Structure:**
  - All documentation in `docs/` directory (SSOT location)
  - One document per topic (no duplicates)
  - Organize by category: `api/`, `architecture/`, `deployment/`, `features/`, `operations/`
  - Archive outdated docs to `docs/archive/`

- **Document Types (Simplified):**
  - **PLAN**: Future work to be done - `[FEATURE]_PLAN.md`
  - **STATUS**: Current state of active work - `[FEATURE]_STATUS.md` or use `docs/project-management/PROJECT_STATUS.md`
  - **ARCHIVE**: Historical/completed work - move to `docs/archive/[category]/`
  - **GUIDE**: Permanent reference documentation - `[TOPIC]_GUIDE.md` or `[topic]-guide.md`
  - **NO MORE**: COMPLETE, SUMMARY, REPORT, PROPOSAL (consolidate into above types)

- **File Naming:**
  - Guides: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.md` for major guides: `API_REFERENCE.md`, `DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md`
  - Plans/Status: `[FEATURE]_PLAN.md`, `[FEATURE]_STATUS.md`
  - Feature docs: `kebab-case.md` for feature-specific: `password-manager-guide.md`
  - Use descriptive names that indicate content

- **Document Structure:**
  ```markdown
  # Title
  
  **Last Updated**: Month Year  
  **Status**: [Active | Deprecated]
  
  ## Overview
  Brief description (1-2 sentences)
  
  ## Table of Contents (if > 3 sections)
  
  ## Main Content
  Clear sections with headers
  
  ## Related Documentation
  - [Link to related doc](./path/to/doc.md)
  ```

- **Content Guidelines:**
  - Start with overview/quick start
  - Include practical examples
  - Cross-reference related docs
  - Keep it concise - remove redundancy
  - Update "Last Updated" when modifying

- **Consolidation Rules:**
  - **Before creating new doc**: Check if topic exists
  - **If duplicate found**: Merge into existing doc
  - **If outdated**: Archive to `docs/archive/`
  - **If similar topics**: Combine into single comprehensive guide

- **Documentation Categories:**
  - `docs/api/` - API references and guides
  - `docs/architecture/` - System architecture and design
  - `docs/deployment/` - Deployment guides and procedures
  - `docs/development/` - Development tools and setup
  - `docs/features/` - Feature-specific documentation
  - `docs/operations/` - Operations and troubleshooting
  - `docs/getting-started/` - Quick start and onboarding

- **When to Consolidate:**
  - Multiple files covering same topic → Merge into one
  - Status/completion reports → Archive after 30 days
  - Duplicate information → Keep most comprehensive version
  - Outdated guides → Archive or update

- **Code Examples in Docs:**
  ```markdown
  ```bash
  # Clear command examples
  docker-compose up -d
  ```
  
  ```typescript
  // Include context and comments
  const example = useExample();
  ```
  ```

- **Cross-References:**
  - Use relative paths: `[Deployment Guide](./deployment/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md)`
  - Update `docs/README.md` when adding new docs
  - Link related sections within same doc

- **Maintenance:**
  - Review quarterly for outdated content
  - Archive completion/status reports monthly
  - Update "Last Updated" dates
  - Remove broken links

- **Document Type Lifecycle:**
  - **PLAN** → Created when work is planned
  - **PLAN** → **STATUS** when work starts
  - **STATUS** → **ARCHIVE** when work completes (after 30 days)
  - **GUIDE** → Permanent, update in place

- **Consolidation Rules:**
  - **PLAN + STATUS + COMPLETE** → Merge into single STATUS file
  - **SUMMARY + COMPLETE** → Move to ARCHIVE after 30 days
  - **REPORT** → Move to ARCHIVE (keep comprehensive audits, archive routine reports)
  - **PROPOSAL** → Convert to PLAN if approved, ARCHIVE if rejected
  - **Multiple status files** → Consolidate into `docs/project-management/PROJECT_STATUS.md`

- **Consolidation Best Practices:**
  - **Before Creating New Doc**: Check `docs/README.md` and search for existing documentation
  - **Status Files**: Use single `docs/project-management/PROJECT_STATUS.md` for overall status
  - **Feature Status**: Use `docs/features/[feature]/STATUS.md` only if needed
  - **Archive Organization**: `docs/archive/[category]/[date]/` - organize by category and date
  - **Archive Categories**: `completion-reports/`, `diagnostics/`, `plans/`, `reports/`, `feature-status/`
  - **Regular Cleanup**: Archive completion/status reports after 30 days, diagnostics after 90 days
  - **Reference**: See [Documentation Types Proposal](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_TYPES_PROPOSAL.md) for details

Follow [SSOT Guidance](mdc:docs/architecture/SSOT_GUIDANCE.md) for single source of truth principles.
